In addition to the @Andremoniy [answer][1], following is the updated and complete answer:

 - First you need to add the following schema/metadata in your beans
   config file:
```
xmlns:tx=&quot;http://www.springframework.org/schema/tx&quot;
```
 - Then you need to update the `xsi:schemaLocation` tag with below
   schema location:
```
http://www.springframework.org/schema/tx
http://www.springframework.org/schema/tx/spring-tx.xsd
```

 - Now declare your respective transaction manager using any
   of below:
```
&lt;!-- If using hibernate --&gt;
&lt;bean id=&quot;transactionManager&quot; name=&quot;transactionManager&quot; class=&quot;org.springframework.orm.hibernate4.HibernateTransactionManager&quot;&gt;
    &lt;property name=&quot;sessionFactory&quot; ref=&quot;sessionFactory&quot;/&gt;
